The paper discusses the interconnectivity and security of production machines in the context of IIoT, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also presents a new approach for collecting and analyzing data, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed model, which involves distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
